+   `ATTEST_NOT_APPLICABLE` is mapped to `WARN`, but this helper only derives `notes` from non-PASS checks. With an empty `checks` list, the synthetic residual MetricReport carries `notes=None`, and `reduce_reports()` drops the explanatory context entirely. `ResidualMetric.evaluate()` emits an explicit reason for the same verdict (`src/metrics/residual.py:166-170`), so the current Control-plane projection can surface an unexplained WARN on the no-log path.
+2. Comment - tests/test_task_runner_trust_gate.py:209-269
